      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 25
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "This 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the refined 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant equipped with VarioCam Plus, delivering a linear power band and a distinct boxer note. Mated to a crisp G96 6-speed manual transaxle, the drivetrain remains tight with precise shift gates and consistent clutch take-up. The chassis benefits from a well-sorted multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson struts, providing excellent lateral grip and communicative feedback through the hydraulic steering rack. Notable mechanical highlights include a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal, addressing critical longevity concerns for this platform. Decelerative force is managed by four-piston Brembo monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors, ensuring optimal thermal management and pedal feel. This is a mechanically transparent, driver-focused example ready for the curves.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
